## Open questions and naming to confirm

These are the points this document could not settle on its own and that
the operator or spec-author needs to decide. They are collected here so
they are not lost; none of them blocks a first draft of the structured
spec, but each changes a detail of it.

- **Detector name.** "Photo Detector (PD)" versus the existing and more
  common "Detector". Recommend standardising on one term across UI,
  catalogue, and docs.
- **R1 axis definition.** Confirm the working interpretation in §7: for a
  horizontal left-to-right central ray, R1 spins the element about that
  ray axis (the element's primary normal pointing back along the CR). If
  the intended axis is different, the whole rotation model re-anchors.
- **Ctrl + wheel for R2.** Confirm this against the strong system "zoom"
  convention, or decide to make the wheel-modifier map configurable.
- **Ribbon tab set.** The proposed Build / Element / Trace-View /
  Experiment / Settings tabs are a starting point; the operator should
  confirm or reshape the top-level grouping.
- **Side-ray and schematic conventions.** The exact number and offset of
  side rays, schematic element thickness, and how reflected vs
  transmitted groups are drawn together — these need agreed drawing
  conventions before the schematic is specified.
- **Analyzer naming.** Whether a polarizer placed after the sample is
  surfaced to the user as an "analyzer" (its role) or simply as another
  LP/CP. Affects the catalogue and the help text.
- **Where groups and collections live in storage.** How element groups
  and experiment collections map onto the existing project file and
  beam-tree model is for the spec-author; this document only fixes the
  user-facing behaviour.

