## Glossary

- **OT — Optical Table.** The top-down working surface.
- **OE — Optical Element.** The basic placeable unit.
- **Active element.** The currently selected element; all editing acts
  on it and it is drawn distinctly.
- **LS — Light Source.** Emits the ray group.
- **PD — Photo Detector.** Terminates the ray group (name under review).
- **LP / CP — Linear / Circular Polarizer.**
- **S — Sample.** The material(s) under study.
- **RG — Ray Group.** Central ray plus four side rays.
- **CR — Central Ray.** The main drawn ray.
- **RRG / TRG — Reflected / Transmitted Ray Group.**
- **IRG — Incident Ray Group.** The ray group falling on an element.
- **PP — Placement Point.** The point that snaps an element onto the CR.
- **R1 / R2 / R3.** The three element rotations, measured relative to the
  incident central ray; R3 is locked by default.
- **Element group.** One or more elements placed on or removed from the
  CR path as a unit.
- **Experiment collection.** A set of experiments around the same
  sample(s).
